==Singing career== In 2010, Bissonnette launched a singing career<ref>[http://www.journaldequebec.com/2016/09/05/5-chansons-marquantes-de-bob-bissonnette ''Le Journal de Québec'': 5 chansons marquantes de Bob Bissonnette]. Le chanteur et ancien hockeyeur aura marqué l'imaginaire des ligues de garage {{fr icon}}</ref> releasing three albums, ''Recrue de l'année'' (2010), ''Les Barbes de séries'' (2012) and ''Rockstar'' (2014). He had a number of singles including "Mettre du tape su' ma palette" and "Recrue de l'année" (2010), "Y sont toutes folles", "Hockey dans rue" and "Chris Chelios" (2011), "Les Barbes de séries" and "La machine à scorer" (2012) and "Rockstar" (2014). He operated completely independently as a musician; he had no contract with any record company, nor did he receive any subsidies from the Canadian government.<ref name="qui etait">[http://www.journaldemontreal.com/2016/09/05/qui-etait-bob-bissonnette Qui était Bob Bissonnette?], in ''[[Le Journal de Montréal]]''; published September 5, 2016; retrieved September 3, 2017</ref>
==Other ventures== Bissonnette was also a minority co-owner, of [[Québec Capitales]]. He performed musical numbers for five years during the regular season of Capitales.<ref>[http://www.journaldemontreal.com/2016/02/23/bob-bissonnette-nouvel-actionnaire-des-capitales-de-quebec ''Le Journal de Montréal'': Bob Bissonnette nouvel actionnaire des Capitales de Québec] {{fr icon}}</ref>
==Death== On 4 September 2016, Bissonnette died in a helicopter accident in the [[Flatlands, New Brunswick|Flatlands]], near [[Campbellton, New Brunswick|Campbellton]], [[New Brunswick]], Canada. The crash also resulted in the death of the pilot Frédérick Décoste. Michel Laplante, president of the Capitales, was injured in the incident.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/new-brunswick/2-killed-helicopter-crash-campbellton-1.3748248 ''CBC News'': Quebec singer Bob Bissonnette, pilot killed in helicopter crash near Campbellton, N.B.]</ref>
