'''JOC Group Inc.''', is a provider of global intelligence for trade, transportation and logistics professionals.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mrweb.com/drno/news20019.htm|title=Daily Research News Online no. 20019 - IHS to Buy Maritime BI Firm JOC Group|website=www.mrweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> It is founded in 1827 and is currently headquartered in Newark, New Jersey. Owned by [[IHS Inc.]],<ref name=":1" /> its brands include [[The Journal of Commerce]],<ref name=":2">{{cite web|last=Fell |first=Jason |url=http://www.foliomag.com/2009/ubm-merges-global-trade-magazines |title=UBM Merges Global Trade Magazines - B2B |publisher=Foliomag.com |date=2009-01-23 |accessdate=2011-01-28}}</ref> [[PIERS: The Port Import/Export Reporting Service]], and a number of directory databases covering the international trade, railroad, and trucking markets.<ref name=":0" /> The JOC Group also stages about 11 conferences and exhibitions serving international trade and maritime markets.

== The Journal of Commerce ==
The organization runs [[The Journal of Commerce]] as a weekly news magazine, which provides news in various categories, including [[Maritime transport|maritime]], [[Port|ports]], [[Rail transport|rail]] and [[intermodal freight transport|intermodal]], [[Road transport|trucking]], [[air cargo]], [[Logistics|international logistics]], [[Regulation|government regulation]] and policy, economy watch, international trade news, [[market data]], and annual review and outlook.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=626789|title=Terms of Service Violation|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-08-02}}</ref> It has a circulation of approximately 15,000. The ''Journal'' also has an online edition, providing content as well as advertising opportunities to its clients. The website features a webcast and white papers in addition to its news and analysis sections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.joc.com/|title=JOC.com {{!}} Container shipping and trade news and analysis|website=www.joc.com|language=en|access-date=2018-08-02}}</ref>

Through its brands including The Journal of Commerce, JOC Group provides import and export trade information to more than 1,600 companies, governments, and associations in more than 50 countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ihsmarkit.com/btp/joc-group.html|title=JOC Group Has Been Acquired {{!}} IHS Markit|website=ihsmarkit.com|access-date=2018-08-02}}</ref>

==History==
Electra acquired JOC Group Inc., in April 2013 from UK based events-led marketing services and communications company [[UBM plc]].<ref>Electra. [https://web.archive.org/web/20130724050137/http://www.electrapartners.com/Media-Centre/?itemid=MTIwNjEzMDUwNDU2MDE= "Electra Partners acquires UBM plc’s Data Services businesses"],</ref> The company changed its name to JOC Group Inc., following that acquisition (previously UBM Global Trade Inc.).<ref name=":2" />

[[IHS Inc.]], announced in November 2014 that it had signed a definitive agreement to acquire JOC Group Inc.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">IHS [http://press.ihs.com/press-release/corporate-financial/ihs-announces-agreement-acquire-joc-group-worlds-leading-supplie-0 "IHS Announces Agreement to Acquire JOC Group, the World’s Leading Supplier of U.S. Seaborne Import and Export Trade Data"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150116083817/http://press.ihs.com/press-release/corporate-financial/ihs-announces-agreement-acquire-joc-group-worlds-leading-supplie-0 |date=2015-01-16 }}</ref>

