{{Infobox person | name = Sabine Getty | image = Dîner de lancement de la collaboration Chatelles x TNT.jpg | alt = | caption = Getty (left) with [[Princess Elisabeth von Thurn und Taxis]] and François du Chastel in 2016 | birth_name = Sabine Ghanem | birth_date = | birth_place = Geneva, Switzerland | education = | alma_mater = [[Gemological Institute of America]] | occupation = Jewelry designer, socialite | years_active = 2012–present | spouse = {{marriage|Joseph Getty|2015}} | children = 1 | parents = | family = Ghanem, [[Getty family|Getty]] | website = {{URL|https://sabinegetty.com/}} | imagesize = | othername = Sabine G }}
'''Sabine Getty''' (née '''Ghanem''') is a Swiss-born English jewelry designer and [[socialite]].
==Early life== Ghanem was born and raised in Geneva, Switzerland.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/sabine-getty-married-jewelry-designer|title=Jewelry Designer Sabine Getty Rocks the Boat|last=Bagley|first=Christopher|work=W Magazine|access-date=2017-05-20|language=en}}</ref> Her father is a Lebanese financier and her Egyptian mother, Karine Ratl, is an interior decorator.<ref name=":0" /> Ghanem speaks English, French and Arabic. She studied theatre and opera before switching to design.{{Citation needed|date=May 2017}} She graduated from the [[Gemological Institute of America]] in 2012<ref name=":0" /> before moving to London.<ref>http://www.wmagazine.com/people/insiders/2015/03/sabine-ghanem-jewelry-designer/</ref>
==Sabine G.== Her jewelry line "Sabine G.", is based in London and sold at [[Bergdorf Goodman]] in New York, Maxfield in Los Angeles, [[Browns (fashion boutique)|Browns]] in London, Montaigne Market in Paris, and in stores in Monaco, Vienna, and Beirut<ref>http://www.thecoveteur.com/the-girl-sabine-g-jewelry-designer/</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=http://www.sabineg.com/about|website=Sabine G.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120163825/http://www.sabineg.com/about|archivedate=20 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sabinegetty.com/|title=Sabine Getty|website=Sabine Getty|access-date=2017-05-20}}</ref>
==Personal life== Ghanem married Joseph Getty, son of [[Mark Getty]] and [[Domitilla Harding]] and a grandson of [[John Paul Getty, Jr.|Sir John Paul Getty]], in 2015 in a Catholic ceremony at the [[Santi Apostoli, Rome|Basilica of the Twelve Apostles]] in Rome.<ref>https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/rome-wedding-sabine-ghanem-joseph-getty#18</ref> Her dress was a custom made haute couture gown by [[Elsa Schiaparelli|Schiaparelli]] with a hooded cloak designed by [[François Lesage|Lesage]] and [[Charlotte Olympia]] heels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vogue.com/slideshow/rome-wedding-sabine-ghanem-joseph-getty#12|title=Sabine Ghanem and Joseph Getty's Wedding in Rome|work=Vogue|access-date=2017-05-20|language=en}}</ref>
Wedding guests included [[Princess Elisabeth von Thurn und Taxis]], [[Princess Beatrice of York]], [[Ginevra Elkann]], [[Charlotte Olympia Dellal]], [[Pierre Casiraghi]], [[Julia Restoin Roitfeld]], and Donna [[Bianca Brandolini d’Adda]].<ref>http://www.vogue.com/13287042/sabine-ghanem-joseph-getty-wedding-rome-italy/</ref> A party celebrating the wedding celebrations was hosted at the [[Palazzo Taverna]]. The wedding reception was held at the [[Castello Orsini-Odescalchi|Castle Odescalchi]].<ref>http://www.vogue.com/slideshow/13287056/rome-wedding-sabine-ghanem-joseph-getty/#24</ref><ref>http://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a11060/sabine-g-wedding-photos/</ref>
In 2017 Getty gave birth to a daughter, Gene Honor Getty.<ref>https://en.vogue.me/fashion/news/sabine-getty-jewelry-baby-memphis-collection/</ref>
